A survey in Shanghai and Beijing revealed a rising trend of obesity due to sedentary lifestyles and poor dietary choices.
Experts warn of the health risks associated with being overweight, including cardiovascular diseases and diabetes.
The government aims to reduce obesity rates, but progress has been slow.
In Kuwait, hypnotism has shown promise in treating obesity.
Meanwhile, in Hong Kong, children's excessive consumption of junk food is a growing concern.
The United Arab Emirates faces a diabetes epidemic linked to increasing obesity rates.
Education and preventive measures are crucial to combat this health crisis.
